object.customQuery:
SELECT ReportPeriod, UpdateDt, PolicyRef, ProductVersionIdRef, PolicyNumber, PolicyVersion, TransactionNumber, LineCd, RiskCd, 
RiskTypeCd, SubTypeCd, CoverageCd, FeeCd, EffectiveDt, ExpirationDt,
  InsuranceTypeCd, NewRenewalCd, Limit1, Limit2, Deductible1, Deductible2, AnnualStatementLineCd, MTDWrittenPremiumAmt, 
  TTDWrittenPremiumAmt, YTDWrittenPremiumAmt, MTDWrittenCommissionAmt, 
  YTDWrittenCommissionAmt, TTDWrittenCommissionAmt, MTDWrittenPremiumFeeAmt, YTDWrittenPremiumFeeAmt, TTDWrittenPremiumFeeAmt, 
  MTDWrittenCommissionFeeAmt, YTDWrittenCommissionFeeAmt, 
  TTDWrittenCommissionFeeAmt
  ,case when combinedkey like '%healthyhomes%' then 0 else InforceAmt end  as  InforceAmt
  ,case when combinedkey like '%healthyhomes%' then 0 else LastInforceAmt end  as  LastInforceAmt
  ,case when combinedkey like '%healthyhomes%' then 0 else MonthEarnedPremiumAmt end  as  MonthEarnedPremiumAmt
  ,case when combinedkey like '%healthyhomes%' then 0 else MTDEarnedPremiumAmt end  as  MTDEarnedPremiumAmt
  ,case when combinedkey like '%healthyhomes%' then 0 else YTDEarnedPremiumAmt end  as  YTDEarnedPremiumAmt
  ,case when combinedkey like '%healthyhomes%' then 0 else TTDEarnedPremiumAmt end  as   TTDEarnedPremiumAmt
  ,case when combinedkey like '%healthyhomes%' then 0 else MonthUnearnedAmt end  as  MonthUnearnedAmt
  ,case when combinedkey like '%healthyhomes%' then 0 else UnearnedAmt end  as  UnearnedAmt, RateAreaName,
  CustomerRef,   StateCd, ProducerCd, OccupancyCd, TerritoryCd, TransactionCd, AgencyNumber, StatLineCd, MajorPerilCd, ClassCd, LocationZip, NumOfFamilies, PolicyTerm
  FROM
 policysummarystats 
where reportperiod = date_format(date_add(current_date() , INTERVAL -1 DAY), '%Y%m')

transformations.description: This reusable expression will properly check and format up to 5 dates that may be in the 'YY-MM-DD' format. It assumes that any years before '50 are in the current century, and any years after '50 are in the previous century.
transformations.name: Exp_format_dates

fields.name: out_Date1
fields.expression:
IIF(ISNULL(in_Date1), NULL,
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 0, 2) = '00', 
IIF(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3, 2) <= '50', TO_DATE(SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YY-MM-DD'), TO_DATE('19' || SUBSTR(v_Date1, 3), 'YYYY-MM-DD')),
IIF(IS_DATE(v_Date1, 'YYYY-MM-DD') and DATE_COMPARE(in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD')) > 0 , in_Date1, TO_DATE('1900-01-01', 'YYYY-MM-DD'))))
